{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, word variations can be noisy without being confused with other words because of the large gap between them.",
    "This is one case where the curse of dimensionality became a benefit instead of a problem.",
    "The curse of dimensionality in machine learning refers to the increase in learning difficulty as the number of feature dimensions increase relative to the training data size (Géron, 2019).",
    "Prior to the transformer architecture, the state-of-the-art NLP methods were recurrent neural networks (RNNs{XE \"RNNs:recurrent neural networks\"}) and long short-term Fig. 2 Building the vocabulary for embedding memories (LSTMs).",
    "RNNs process sequential data by maintaining a hidden state that updates with each new input in the sequence."
  ]
}